			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Does anyone feel like being a bard is cheating?<a name="23111"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 23 04 10:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi all. I wanted to ask a question both of Veterans and Newbies like myself. This is my first character, so I am a true Newbie to the game and not just to the bard. I am now a level 20 Bard, and because of overwhelming advice have spent the last 5 levels in the Pauludal Caverns. In my grouping experince I suppose we have had a fairly well rounded group, wiz, clr/sham, bard, beast, zerk, and fighter. My question is this. Do any of you feel like being a bard is cheating. I am in my group asking what they would like of me and the answer is invariably haste, heal, and since I hit 20 mana. Because of the well rounded groups, they don't need the meelee, so I use instruments. I feel like I am cheating. I don't use any mana, I don't generally get involved in meelee or do damage, and I feel like I am leeching experience off the group. In fact my only purpose is taunting off the adds that break through and go after the cleric and wizard. Am I doing something wrong? Should I be doing more. Eventually twisting becomes automatic. I love the class, I love the versitility that means I can do song damage, meelee damage, tank a little, run like the wind and all of the things that make this class great. I just feel like maybe we are too good sometimes. Please respond both newbies and veterans as I want to know if this changes at later levels.
<br />

<br />
Thanks,
<br />
Nyte</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
