			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Does anyone feel like being a bard is cheating?<a name="23153"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 23 04 11:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It is one of the mental parts of being a bard - you dont always get to see the impact of your skill on your group - except that they dont die as much and you succeed more often.  What I mean is, every other class has a positive feed back they get during a battle/adventure etc.  Tanks hack and slash, clerics heal, shamans slow/dot, chanters mez, wizards nuke, druids dot/root - we just sit there getting sore fingers - especally when there is no need to CC or pull.  
<br />

<br />
Most of the time the other group members are too busy to notice that they resisted snare or that mobs are dying easier - I have been a tank with a bard in the group and thought &quot;Man I am hitting better than usual - must be my new Frost&quot; - not realizing that the bard slow had reduced ac by 78.
<br />

<br />
What you should take away from this is your group did well BECAUSE you were there being a bard.  Without you things would have been slower and the rest of the group would have gotten less exp.  
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
