			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Does anyone feel like being a bard is cheating?<a name="23360"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 23 04 10:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At those levels I instrument twisted DDD, Chords, Heal in groups.  Yes, my weapon skills suffered.  I made up for that after lvl 26.  Go to SK and snare-fear Gnolls.  Get a dex buff if you can, and do it until your weapon skills are maxed.
<br />

<br />
The one skill that WILL go up using that twist is DEFENSE.  ALL the adds will hit YOU, hehe.
<br />

<br />
Also, your most important role in a group is using your lvl 15 Mez song on the adds.  Crowd Control, as we call it, will be your most important job.  Without it, at higher levels, you will all surely die, hehe.  There are guides with mezzing tips in them here.
<br />

<br />
Check the Guides section for more details.  Also, take a look at my &quot;Newbies Guide to Aggro and Pulling&quot;.  Your other premiere gig will be Lulling and pulling for groups.  Start doing LDoN missions and hone your skills.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
