			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Does anyone feel like being a bard is cheating?<a name="23733"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 9:25 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Lose the instruments for now.  Group haste is a singing, so no mod there.  Heal with lute is not gonna make that much of a difference, you are better off melee'ing-- it doesn't heal the Mt fast enough and the others shouldn't be getting hit enuff to need it.  Your haste is helping, increasing group melee damage by about 10%.  if they don't need your DPS like you say (Damage Per Second ) then train your off skills like pierce and 1hb.  You shouldn't be taunting adds for 2 reasons :
<br />
1) you suck at it (compared to a real taunting class)
<br />
2) that is why you have a mez song
<br />

<br />
If you think you are cheating try playing 
<br />
cleric -&gt; sit, med, heal when someone is low on health.  Oh yeah, buff 2x an hour -- death by boredom, but you can chat )
<br />
chanter -&gt; buff 2x an hour (haste a bit more), watch the shammy slow, watch the wizard nuke, mez an add every now and then.  If you get bored you can nuke for about what the tank does in 1 hit.  Once or twice a night you get to derail a train ) 
<br />

<br />
To make yourself more useful:
<br />
1) Pull
<br />
2) mez adds
<br />
3) keep manasong up
<br />
4) keep haste up
<br />
5) melee
<br />
6) AE slow -- it generally isn't worth letting the chanter slow at this level as it takes a ton o mana and mobs die too fast.
<br />
</span></td>
