				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Does anyone feel like being a bard is cheating?<a name="23768"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 10:23 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For everything, turn, turn turn..
<br />
There is a season, turn, turn, turn...
<br />

<br />
A time to mellee, a time to drum,
<br />
A time to pull, a time to let the mobs come.
<br />

<br />
A time to swap in your lute,
<br />
A time to sit on your a$ and just look cyuutteeee...
<br />

<br />
Ok /song off.
<br />

<br />
I have felt guilty quite a few times in my years of barding.
<br />

<br />
Telling my group I had to leave for 30 minutes back in LGUK in my late 40s.  They told my not to camp, just sit there and sing mana/regen.  This was back when Frenzy was an uber camp.  So I did, and came back to a ding and a group that thanked me for afking and not camping....
<br />

<br />
Using instruments and meleeing, and seeing &quot;You punch a Gnoll Reaper for 5 melee damage&quot; and &quot;Your skill at Hand to hand has just gone up (57)&quot;.  Bard instrument melee so powah.
<br />

<br />
Realizing that I forgot to swap weapons in halfway through some SSRA boss mob 25 minute fight, and that I had been smacking the mob with my lute rather then Shissar Bane weapons....
<br />

<br />
Being grouped with 4 wizards and a druid on raids, and having them tell me, STOP TWISTING, JUST SING MUSE.
<br />

<br />
There will always be times when you feel you arent contributing, or feel that you arent doing enough.  But remember, click for click, you have pounded more keys per session then any other class ;o)
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
