			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Does anyone feel like being a bard is cheating?<a name="23843"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 12:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You know, I used to, and you will get 'bard envy' about certain things you can do throughout your bardic career.
<br />

<br />
However, I have played nearly every other class and there has not been one of them that could do something well that I wish my bard could do.
<br />

<br />
There is some balance in the game, its just bards get to be 'pretty good' at a number of things.
<br />

<br />
I also, get 'wow, a decent bard' sometimes in a group, like they have never seen one, and that disturbs me a bit.
<br />

<br />
I have also grouped one of my alts with mid level bards and seen only one song in my buff window, if that.  Go figure.
<br />

<br />
The class has  a lot of potential to be played really well and really badly. Any class, played well, in the right circumstances can shine. The reverse is true as well.
<br />

<br />
At 20, imo, other than a cleric, there is no hugely needed class for the most part. As your bard levels, there are groups that could funtion without you that you could literally double there kill rate.  There are groups that might not funtion at all without you.
<br />

<br />
A level 20 bard is not really defined yet, along about 30 when your charm is working, is a big step. The group buffs get better in the forties, and in the 50's the add on buffs start kicking in.
<br />

<br />
It will come, and if you get good, people will think your are nigh on indespensible.
<br />

<br />
It is not always what you do damage wise, or crowd control wise, its sometimes what everyone else can do.  I suspect in a 20's group with three melees, your str buff alone (increasing atk) will account for as much damage as at least one of the other melees. Most players will never realize this, but you will.  Ditto on a damage shield. Somone said don't play health during battle...thats true in some cases, but in aggro sharing groups it can mean excess mana for the cleric vs not quite enough.
<br />

<br />
You aren't cheating, you are playing one of THE premier group enhancers in the game (and a darn fine solo artist as well).
<br />

<br />
Edit...Ok maybe FM is cheating...
<br />
</span></td>
